#: lib/chatbot/graphs/faq/faq_graph.ex:51
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "HATE_SPEECH_DEF"
msgstr "‚úîÔ∏è *Hate speech* involves encouraging, promoting, or inciting, directly or indirectly, hatred, discrimination, or violence against a group or person based on racial, xenophobic, sexual orientation, and other forms of intolerance.\n\n"
"‚ÑπÔ∏è An example of hate speech is the *spreading of negative stereotypes* towards a racialized group online. Often, *disinformation* can foster hatred and discrimination. An example of this was the rumor that Chinese people do not pay taxes (completely false).\n\n"
"Hate speech, when often repeated, *can permeate society* to the point where it goes beyond words and influences behavior, for example, acting differently towards certain people. This is known as *discrimination*.\n\n"
"‚úîÔ∏è *Discrimination* involves differentiating or giving less favorable treatment when there are no relevant differences between people or situations, as well as giving identical treatment to people in situations that are actually different. Discrimination violates a person‚Äôs fundamental rights.\n\n"
"‚ÑπÔ∏è An example of discrimination would be asking a person about their religion during a job interview to assess them as a candidate (or not) for a job. This would be an illegal question that we should not answer, indicating that they are not evaluating us for the job based on our suitability, but rather on personal characteristics unrelated to the job performance.\n\n"
"‚úîÔ∏è Beyond these behaviors is the *hate crime*, which occurs when a person or group attacks another solely motivated by their belonging to a particular social group (real or perceived). This is a criminal act under the Spanish Penal Code (an assault, a robbery, an insult‚Ä¶) motivated by the perpetrator‚Äôs prejudices towards certain perceived characteristics in the victim: skin color, religion, sexual orientation, national origin, etc.\n\n"
"‚ÑπÔ∏è Example: A physical assault motivated by Islamophobia against a woman wearing a hijab.\n\n"
"As you can see, in these definitions *the key is the motivation*. Rejection of a traditionally discriminated group makes hate speech and crimes especially dangerous for coexistence and rights."

